## The Offer Stacking Model

Most solopreneurs think in single products:

"I sell $297 courses"

"I coach at $5K/month"

"I have a $99/month membership"

This is limiting. You're picking one revenue stream and ignoring your audience's full potential.

**Real model: Offer Stacking**

You create a **pyramid of offers** serving the same audience, each at a different price/commitment level:

**Level 1 (Free - Awareness):** Lead magnet (free email course)

**Level 2 ($27-$97 - Entry):** Low-ticket product (ebook, template pack, micro course)

**Level 3 ($297-$997 - Engagement):** Mid-ticket product (course, small group program)

**Level 4 ($2K-$10K - Transformation):** High-ticket service (1-on-1 coaching, consulting)

**Level 5 ($10K-$100K+/year - Done-With-You):** Premium service (ongoing retainer, advisory)

People move up the pyramid as they get results and trust you more.

**Result:** One person could spend:
- $0 (free lead magnet)
- $47 (template pack)
- $497 (course)
- $7,000 (coaching)
- $24,000/year (retainer)

That's $31,544 lifetime value from one person.

Most solopreneurs extract $297 or $5,000. That's it. They're leaving $31K on the table.

---

## The Four Offer Levels

### Level 1: Free Lead Magnet (Awareness)

**What it is:** Free resource (email course, checklist, audit, case study)

**Purpose:** Build your list, demonstrate expertise, attract buyers

**Time to create:** 20-40 hours (one-time)

**Perpetual value:** Hundreds of leads/year for life

**Examples:**
- Free 5-day email course: "Build Your Service Offer in 5 Days"
- Free audit: "Audit your pricing in 15 minutes, get a $2K strategy worth"
- Free workshop: "How to Productize Your Service (90-min live training)"
- Free template: "3-Tier Offer Menu Template"

**Pricing:** FREE

**Volume goal:** 500+ subscribers/month from this

**Monetization:** 2% buy your next offer ($47) = 10 customers × $47 = $470/month from lead magnet

---

### Level 2: Low-Ticket Product ($27-$97)

**What it is:** Self-service product, little-to-no support

**Time to deliver:** 0 minutes (automated, delivered via email/download)

**Price:** $47-$97 (psychological pricing: $47 better than $50)

**Your time to create:** 30-60 hours (one-time, then zero maintenance)

**Volume goal:** 20-50 customer/month

**Revenue:** 30 customers × $67 average = $2,010/month

**Examples:**
- Template pack ($47): 12 templates to productize your service
- Ebook ($29): "The Freelancer's Pricing Guide" (5,000 words, PDF)
- Micro course ($97): "Write Better Sales Pages" (3 videos, 45 min total)
- Checklist pack ($47): 10 checklists for running a solopreneur business

**Customer profile:** People who:
- Know they have a problem
- Can't afford coaching
- Want DIY solution
- Will buy on impulse for $47

**Conversion rate:** 1-5% of people who see it (from email, ads, organic)

**Benefit:** Builds trust. Low risk for buyer. Qualifies them as paying customer.

---

### Level 3: Mid-Ticket Product ($297-$997)

**What it is:** Course, group program, or structured training

**Time to deliver:** Depends (self-paced course = zero time; group program = 50-100 hours/month)

**Price:** $297-$897

**Your time to create:** 80-200 hours (depending on format)

**Volume goal:** 5-15 customers/month

**Revenue:** 10 customers × $497 = $4,970/month

**Examples:**
- Online course ($497): "Build Your Service Offer in 30 Days" (8 modules, 40 videos, workbooks)
- Group program ($797): "12-Week Freelance Content Strategy Bootcamp" (weekly calls + materials)
- Workshop ($297): "One-Day Service to Product Intensive" (6 hours, live Zoom)

**Customer profile:** People who:
- Tried DIY (your $47 product)
- Got 30% of the way
- Want more structure/guidance
- Will invest $297-$997

**Conversion rate:** 5-15% of people who bought your low-ticket product

**Benefit:** Major revenue jump. Real transformation. Builds authority.

---

### Level 4: High-Ticket Service ($2K-$10K)

**What it is:** Coaching, consulting, intensive, small group

**Time to deliver:** 40-100 hours per customer (significant time)

**Price:** $2,000-$10,000 (per engagement)

**Volume goal:** 2-5 customers/month

**Revenue:** 3 customers × $5,000 = $15,000/month

**Examples:**
- 1-on-1 coaching ($5,000): 6 months, bi-weekly calls + email support
- Consulting project ($25,000): 12-week strategy engagement
- Intensive ($7,000): 3-month implementation with weekly calls
- Small group ($3,000): 12-week group program with 8 people max

**Customer profile:** People who:
- Took your course, got results
- Want faster outcomes
- Are ready to invest significant money
- Want high-touch guidance

**Conversion rate:** 5-20% of course graduates

**Benefit:** High revenue per customer. Deeper relationships. Real transformation. Authority building.

---

### Level 5: Premium Retainer ($10K-$100K+/year)

**What it is:** Ongoing advisory, fractional CEO, mastermind

**Time to deliver:** 10-20 hours/month (very efficient)

**Price:** $10K-$25K/month retainer

**Volume goal:** 1-3 retainer clients

**Revenue:** 2 retainers × $15K/month = $30,000/month

**Examples:**
- Executive advisor ($15K/month): Ongoing strategic guidance for SaaS founder
- Fractional CMO ($10K/month): Monthly strategy + 10 hours/month support
- Premium mastermind ($5K/month per member, 10 members): Curated peer group + monthly calls

**Customer profile:** People who:
- Have worked with you before
- Got major results from coaching/consulting
- See you as essential to their business
- Can afford premium pricing

**Conversion rate:** 10-30% of high-ticket clients become retainer clients

**Benefit:** Highest revenue per hour. Most predictable. Least stressful. Real strategic work.

